</summary><content type="html">&lt;p&gt;This is my second attempt at a hammock stand. Like &lt;a class="reference external" href="https://thomaschamberlin.com/hammock-stand-v1.html"&gt;the first&lt;/a&gt;, it will hold three hammocks, but this resolves a few issues that I've had with the first one since getting it built:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Primarily, this iteration will be significantly larger. The first stand was far too short, and takes some finagling in order to prevent the hammocks from touching the ground.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;I'll also be using some sort of hardwood and properly staining/sealing it for outdoor use -- the first stand was made with construction pine and is not very attractive and won't last long without painting.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Finally, I now own an orbital sander, so I'll be able to prevent issues with splinters.&lt;/p&gt;
